      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "Puzzle games are a genre that is flooded with unfortunate mediocrity, I feel. At the time of writing this review, puzzle games sit with a little under 1500 options available on the Nintendo eShop, the third most populated game genre behind action games and adventure games. Of course, there are the gems that everyone knows within that library but each has their own qualities that set it apart from their competitors. Whether it be the whimsy of "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            0
          ],
          1,
          "Untitled Goose Game"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          ", the rule bending ingenuity of "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            0
          ],
          1,
          "Baba is You"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          " or the surprising challenge that the removal of a single mechanic can prove to be in "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            0
          ],
          1,
          "Captain Toad: Treasure Tracker"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "; what these games have in common is something to convince you to pick them up a second time, something that grabs you immediately to let you know that it is an experience worth investing your time in, something that a puzzle game needs given how heavily it relies on its only aspect of gameplay - its puzzles - when other genres can fall back on things like story or a diversity of mechanics. When it comes to "
        ],
        [
          0,
          [
            0
          ],
          1,
          "World Splitter"
        ],
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          ", I believe it deserves its place amongst the games listed above, with its gameplay centred on such an interesting and challenging concept that any fan of puzzle games will know its quality with a single touch of the right stick on level one. "
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      10,
      0
    ],
    [
      1,
      "h3",
      [
        [
          0,
