          0,
          "Each world, that is to say grouping of 10 levels, has two backdrops in each level. These tend to be opposites when it comes to their design. For example in World - I, one backdrop is a turquoise coloured field with spacely-placed trees while the other is a lavender fading into cream coloured sky with tall, leafless trees. In World - II, we have a peachy pink and orange sky with a tropic design, contrasted with a deep sapphire coloured world and a background of a city’s skyline. The levels are pleasant to look at but also visually dissimilar enough to not cause accidental confusion between the worlds."
        ]
      ]
    ],
