    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "The music design is somewhat reserved. Each world alternates between two songs for each level, ranging from calming keyboards and bass guitars, to ethereal xylophone and harps, to upbeat pianos and plucky string instruments. Overall, the music is a pleasant addition to the game but the lack of variety can feel samey after a while. Imagine getting stuck on a level for a long while, beating it and breezing through to the next, only to be met with another level with the same song you just listened to for 20 minutes. "
        ]
      ]
